<h2>PHP to JavaScript</h2>
A lot of web developers grew up with PHP. PHP gets a lot of criticism and some [people](http://firsttube.com/read/An-Argument-for-PHP/)   provide some valid counter arguments.  I will be dead neutral on this issue until my first RoR application is up and running. I was wondering, if one could create a small CASE tool that could convert PHP into JavaScript and here is what I came up with.

<div  class="code-block console-wrap"><div class="code code-block">

class SimpleClass
{
    // property declaration
    public $var = 'a default value';

    // method declaration
    public function displayVar() {
        echo $this->var;
    }
}
</div>

<div  class="msg" class="msg">
</div>
<div class="console"></div>

<ol class="results"></ol> 

</div>


This can be written in Javascript in various ways one way is:

<div  class="code-block console-wrap"><div class="code code-block">
<code>
function SimpleClass()
{
    // property declaration
   var $var = 'a default value';

    // method declaration
   this.displayVar = function () {
        alert($var);
    }
}

n= new SimpleClass();
n.displayVar();

</code>
</div>

<div  class="msg" class="msg">
</div>
<div class="console"></div>
<button class="eval">Run Code!</button>
<ol class="results"></ol> 
<img src="http://localhost/codeigniter/images/jquery.png" style="float:right; width:85px"/>
</div>


